</p>
<p>
    <strong>MALAYSIA PROFESSIONAL ACCOUNTANCY CENTRE (“MyPAC”) PROGRAMME: –</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>OFFER OF MEMBERSHIP IN MyPAC</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>1. </strong>
    <strong>INTRODUCTION</strong>
</p>
<p>
    1.1. <strong>CONGRATULATIONS! </strong>We are pleased to inform you that you have been selected to be a member of MyPAC.
</p>
<p>
    1.2. As a member you will benefit from MyPAC’s collaboration with identified training service providers who will provide world class and innovative tuition
    delivery to attain higher success rate on your ACCA exams. You are eligible to access a leading and cutting-edge online classroom from our designated
    centres provided by our partners.
</p>
<p>
    1.3. As part of the MyPAC membership, you would have undergone or will be required to undergo various assessments such as, and not limited to, Learning
    Ability Test, English Test and Occupational Individual Profile (“<strong>Baseline Assessments</strong>”). These assessments are to help MyPAC understand
    your strength level and to provide you with the necessary steps for improvement. These assessments will be fully sponsored by MyPAC and will determine the
    commencement date of your programme.
</p>
<p>
    1.4. As a member of MyPAC, you are required to:
</p>
<p>
    i. be a member of Malaysian Institute of Accountants (“<strong>MIA</strong>”) upon qualifying as a member of the institute within a year of completing your
    course;
</p>
<p>
    ii. commit and provide MyPAC with a minimum of 100 hours of voluntary work to support MyPAC’s activities particularly in recruiting more Bumiputeras to
    take the professional exams upon the completion of your course; and
</p>
<p>
    iii. undertake any other tasks/activities identified from time to time by MyPAC (for example: to be future students’ mentors or coaches).
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>2. </strong>
    <strong>BENEFITS</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
    2.1 Subject to the terms and conditions of the membership, as a member of MyPAC you may be eligible for financial assistance, learning materials, training
    opportunities, mentoring and any other available support during the period of your study, which will be solely determined by MyPAC.
</p>
<p>
    2.2 The financial assistance will only be provided to MyPAC members for a one-time exam sitting within the sponsorship period. If the member fails in any
    of the examination taken, MyPAC may at its full discretion determine whether to allow the member to retake the examination or otherwise. The member pays
    all the cost for the examination retakes. MyPAC may in its absolute discretion determine whether:-
</p>
<p>
    i. to reimburse the examination cost to the Recipient for the examination that the Recipient has successfully passed, provided the Recipient must provide
    MyPAC with the relevant proof of payment receipt and certification showing that the Recipient has passed the examination; or
</p>
<p>
    ii. to terminate this offer.
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>3. </strong>
    <strong>CONDITIONS PRECEDENT</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
    3.1 This offer is a <strong>conditional offer </strong>subject to you fulfilling the following conditions (unless waived by MyPAC at its absolute
    discretion):
</p>
<p>
    i. complete the assessment tests;
</p>
<p>
    ii. undergo a compulsory medical check-up and you must be certified as being in good health and free from contagious/ infectious diseases or illness that
    will adversely affect your study. MyPAC has the right to withdraw this offer or to terminate you from the programme if you are found to suffer from or to
    be a carrier of contagious/ infectious diseases, or to suffer from a medical condition requiring continuous medical care;
</p>
<p>
    iii. execute our Declaration and Undertaking form and execution of a formal contract;
</p>
<p>
    iv. submit of all required ‘certified true copy’ documents;
</p>
<p>
    v. attend English enhancement programmes planned for individual candidates and be subjected to reassessment of your English level to determine whether you
    meet the desired result required by MyPAC at its discretion and MyPAC shall determine whether to make this offer unconditional or otherwise;
</p>
<p>
    vi. attend all classes and programmes during your Probation Period. For the purpose of this paragraph, “<strong>Probation Period</strong>” means such
    period of time to be determined solely by MyPAC at its discretion during which the MyPAC members will be assessed and evaluated for suitability for full
    membership;
</p>
<p>
    vii. MyPAC may at its absolute discretion assist to secure and/or provide funding for all MyPAC candidates as follows: -
</p>
<p>
    <strong>a. </strong>
    <strong>Funding by MyPAC</strong>
</p>
<p>
    MyPAC’s funding to candidates are determined based on criteria(s) set by MyPAC at its absolute discretion; or
</p>
<p>
    <strong>b. </strong>
    <strong>Funding by Other Funders</strong>
</p>
<p>
    In respect of other funders, MyPAC shall have the right to propose you to any appropriate funders for their consideration to provide you with funding,
    subject to you meeting their criteria(s). Additionally, you will be required to comply with any requirements stipulated by the appropriate funder. Only
    upon your successful procurement and acceptance of the funding from the appropriate funder makes this offer unconditional. For avoidance of doubt, should
    you decide not to accept the funding offered, this offer is deemed withdrawn automatically and terminated by MyPAC; and any other requirement(s) notified
    to you in writing by MyPAC.
</p>
<p>
    3.2 You are not allowed to postpone any planned programmes, professional certification courses and exams without any reason, except with the consent in
    writing from MyPAC.
</p>
<p>
    3.3 MyPAC will inform you in writing whether you have successfully met the required criteria as stipulated in item 3.1. MyPAC will make its assessment at
    its absolute discretion. MyPAC’s decision to this is final and irrevocable. MyPAC shall not have any obligation to provide any explanation to justify
    MyPAC’s decision and any request for reconsideration/appeal shall simply be rejected.
</p>
<p>
    3.4 Any cost incurred whatsoever in performance of this Clause 3.1 is borne by you and any advance payment made by MyPAC on your behalf in relation to the
    same shall be refunded back to MyPAC (within a reasonable period), unless you meet the required criteria set by MyPAC. In such event, the costs will form
    part of the total costs of the sponsorships, which will be subjected to the performance and clauses of sponsorship agreement to be signed by MyPAC and you.
</p>
<p>
    <strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
